template.name: Template Net YAMAHA RT SNMP
template.description: Template YAMAHA Router monitoring template using SNMPv1.

item.name: SNMP Trap: YAMAHA-RT-HARDWARE::yrhMemoryUtilTrap
item.description:
This trap indicates that the value of the variable yrhMemoryUtil is over the value of the variable yrhMemoryUtilTrapThreshold.
Varbinds: 0. yrhMemoryUtil (GAUGE) The utilization in percentage of main memory.

item.name: SNMP Trap: YAMAHA-RT-HARDWARE::yrhCpuUtilTrap
item.description:
This trap indicates that the CPU utilization is over the threshold value.
Varbinds: 0. yrhCpuUtil5sec (GAUGE) The average utilization of CPU in 5 seconds.
1. yrhCpuUtil1min (GAUGE) The average utilization of CPU in 1 minutes.
2. yrhCpuUtil5min (GAUGE) The average utilization of CPU in 5 minutes.

item.name: SNMP Trap: YAMAHA-RT-HARDWARE::yrhSystemAlarmTrap
item.description:
This trap indicates that the system ALARM LED is on. At the option, the variables, yrhPowerModuleStatus and yrhFanModuleStatus for each module, will follow in the variable-bindings field
Varbinds: 0. yrhInboxTemperature (GAUGE) A temperature in the box.

item.name: SNMP Trap: YAMAHA-RT-HARDWARE::yrhMultiCpuUtilTrap
item.description:
This trap indicates that the multi CPU utilization is over the threshold value.
Varbinds: 0. yrhMultiCpuIndex (INTEGER) A unique value for each CPU.
1. yrhMultiCpuName (OCTETSTR) A name of the CPU.
2. yrhMultiCpuUtil5sec (GAUGE) The average utilization of CPU in 5 seconds.
3. yrhMultiCpuUtil1min (GAUGE) The average utilization of CPU in 1 minutes.
4. yrhMultiCpuUtil5min (GAUGE) The average utilization of CPU in 5 minutes.

item.name: SNMP Trap: YAMAHA-RT-HARDWARE::yrhCpuThresholdOver
item.description:
This trap indicates that the CPU utilization was over the threshold value.
Varbinds: 0. yrhCpuUtil5sec (GAUGE) The average utilization of CPU in 5 seconds.

item.name: SNMP Trap: YAMAHA-RT-HARDWARE::yrhCpuThresholdUnder
item.description:
This trap indicates that the CPU utilization was under the threshold value.
Varbinds: 0. yrhCpuUtil5sec (GAUGE) The average utilization of CPU in 5 seconds.

item.name: SNMP Trap: YAMAHA-RT-HARDWARE::yrhMemoryThresholdOver
item.description:
This trap indicates that the MEMORY utilization was over the threshold value.
Varbinds: 0. yrhMemoryUtil (GAUGE) The utilization in percentage of main memory.

item.name: SNMP Trap: YAMAHA-RT-HARDWARE::yrhMemoryThresholdUnder
item.description:
This trap indicates that the MEMORY utilization was under the threshold value.
Varbinds: 0. yrhMemoryUtil (GAUGE) The utilization in percentage of main memory.

item.name: SNMP Trap: YAMAHA-RT-FIRMWARE::yrfLoginTrap
item.description:
This trap indicates that the login status is changed.
Varbinds: 0. yrfLoginIndex (INTEGER) A unique value for each login.
1. yrfLoginProtocol (INTEGER) Indicates that anyone is now login or not from status.
2. yrfLoginStatus (INTEGER) Indicates that anyone is now login or not from status.
3. yrfLoginFromIp (IPADDR) An IP address which access to the system by TELNET/SSH.

item.name: SNMP Trap: YAMAHA-RT-INTERFACES::yrIfIsdnStatusChange
item.description:
This trap signifies that an ISDN status of index/bch is changed.
Varbinds: 0. yrIfIsdnIndex (INTEGER) A unique value for each BRI or PRI interface. This value is equal to yrIfBriIndex/yrIfPriIndex and yrIfIndex for a correspond interface.
1. yrIfIsdnBch (INTEGER) A B-channel number of a BRI/PRI interface. For a BRI, the valid numbers are only 1 and 2. For a PRI, the numbers 1 through 23 are valid.

item.name: SNMP Trap: YAMAHA-RT-INTERFACES::yrIfPpLinkDown
item.description:
This trap signifies that a PP interface is down.
Varbinds: 0. yrIfPpIndex (INTEGER) A unique value for each interface. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of ifNumber. The value for each interface must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re- initialization.

item.name: SNMP Trap: YAMAHA-RT-INTERFACES::yrIfPpLinkUp
item.description:
This trap signifies that a PP interface is up.
Varbinds: 0. yrIfPpIndex (INTEGER) A unique value for each interface. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of ifNumber. The value for each interface must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re- initialization.

item.name: SNMP Trap: YAMAHA-RT-INTERFACES::yrIfPpUtilTrap
item.description:
This trap signifies that the change of the utilization of a PP interface crosses the threshold.
Varbinds: 0. yrIfPpIndex (INTEGER) A unique value for each interface. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of ifNumber. The value for each interface must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re- initialization.
1. yrIfPpOutUtil (GAUGE) The utilization of the output packet traffic. The unit is a percent (%).
2. yrIfPpInUtil (GAUGE) The utilization of the input packet traffic. The unit is a percent (%).

item.name: SNMP Trap: YAMAHA-RT-INTERFACES::yrIfTunnelLinkDown
item.description:
This trap signifies that a TUNNEL interface is down.
Varbinds: 0. yrIfTunnelIndex (INTEGER) A unique value for each TUNNEL interface. This value is equal to yrIfIndex for a correspond interface.

item.name: SNMP Trap: YAMAHA-RT-INTERFACES::yrIfTunnelLinkUp
item.description:
This trap signifies that a TUNNEL interface is up.
Varbinds: 0. yrIfTunnelIndex (INTEGER) A unique value for each TUNNEL interface. This value is equal to yrIfIndex for a correspond interface.

item.name: SNMP Trap: YAMAHA-RT-INTERFACES::yrIfPpAnonymousLinkDownWithUsername
item.description:
This trap signifies that a PP Anonymous interface is down with connected username.
Varbinds: 0. yrIfPpIndex (INTEGER) A unique value for each interface. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of ifNumber. The value for each interface must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re- initialization.
1. yrIfPpAnonymousUsername (OCTETSTR) A connected username for each PP Anonymous interface.

item.name: SNMP Trap: YAMAHA-RT-INTERFACES::yrIfPpAnonymousLinkUpWithUsername
item.description:
This trap signifies that a PP Anonymous interface is up with connected username.
Varbinds: 0. yrIfPpIndex (INTEGER) A unique value for each interface. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of ifNumber. The value for each interface must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re- initialization.
1. yrIfPpAnonymousUsername (OCTETSTR) A connected username for each PP Anonymous interface.

item.name: SNMP Trap: YAMAHA-RT-INTERFACES::yrIfMobileStatusTrap
item.description:
This trap signifies that a number of antenna of signal strength became below the threshold.
Varbinds: 0. yrIfMobileIndex (INTEGER) A unique value for each mobile information. This value is equal to yrIfIndex for a correspond information.
1. yrIfMobileAntennaLevel (INTEGER) A number of antenna of signal strength.
2. yrIfMobileDbm (INTEGER) A dBm of signal strength.
3. yrIfMobileSignalQuality (INTEGER) A signal quality of signal strength.

item.name: SNMP Trap: YAMAHA-RT-INTERFACES::yrIfWwanModStatTrp
item.description:
This trap signifies that a number of antenna of signal strength became below the threshold.
Varbinds: 0. yrIfWwanModIndex (INTEGER) A unique value for each WWAN module information. This value is equal to yrIfIndex for a correspond information.
1. yrIfWwanModAntLevel (INTEGER) A state of antenna of signal strength.

item.name: SNMP Trap: YAMAHA-RT-IP::yrIpKeepaliveDown
item.description:
This trap signifies that a IP keepalive status is down.
Varbinds: 0. yrIpKeepaliveIndex (INTEGER) A unique value for each configuration of IP keepalive.

item.name: SNMP Trap: YAMAHA-RT-IP::yrIpKeepaliveUp
item.description:
This trap signifies that a IP keepalive status is up.
Varbinds: 0. yrIpKeepaliveIndex (INTEGER) A unique value for each configuration of IP keepalive.

item.name: SNMP Trap: YAMAHA-RT-IP::yrIpHeartBeat
item.description:
This trap signifies that heartbeat packet has not received for a given period.
Varbinds: 0. yrIpHeartBeatIndex (INTEGER) A index for heartbeat infomation.
1. yrIpHeartBeatName (OCTETSTR) A unique name of a state nnotified of heartbeat packet.

item.name: SNMP Trap: YAMAHA-RT-IP::yrIpHeartbeat2
item.description:
This trap signifies that heartbeat2 packet has not received for a given period.
Varbinds: 0. yrIpHeartbeat2Index (INTEGER) A index for heartbeat2 infomation.
1. yrIpHeartbeat2Name (OCTETSTR) A unique name of a state nnotified of heartbeat2 packet.

item.name: SNMP Trap: YAMAHA-RT-SWITCH::yrSwFindSwitch
item.description:
This trap signifies that a controlled switch is detected.
Varbinds: 0. yrSwNumber (INTEGER) The number of controlled switch on this system.
1. yrSwProduct (INTEGER) The product number.
2. yrSwPhysAddress (OCTETSTR) The controlled switch's MAC Address

item.name: SNMP Trap: YAMAHA-RT-SWITCH::yrSwDetectDown
item.description:
This trap signifies that a controlled switch is lost.
Varbinds: 0. yrSwNumber (INTEGER) The number of controlled switch on this system.
1. yrSwProduct (INTEGER) The product number.
2. yrSwPhysAddress (OCTETSTR) The controlled switch's MAC Address

item.name: SNMP Trap: YAMAHA-RT-SWITCH::yrSwFanLock
item.description:
This trap signifies that a controlled switch's fan lock.
Varbinds: 0. yrSwFanStatus (INTEGER) The status of controlled switch's fan.

item.name: SNMP Trap: YAMAHA-RT-SWITCH::yrSwOverSupply
item.description:
This trap signifies that a controlled switch's PoE over supply.
Varbinds: 0. yrSwSupply (INTEGER) The supplied value of controlled switch's power unit.

item.name: SNMP Trap: YAMAHA-RT-SWITCH::yrSwOverTemp
item.description:
This trap signifies that a controlled switch's over temperature.
Varbinds: 0. yrSwTemp (INTEGER) The controlled switch's temperature.

item.name: SNMP Trap: YAMAHA-RT-SWITCH::yrSwPowerUnitFailure
item.description:
This trap signifies that a controlled switch's Power unit failure.
Varbinds: 0. yrSwPowerFailure (INTEGER) The status of controlled switch's power unit.

item.name: SNMP Trap: YAMAHA-RT-SWITCH::yrSwLoopDetectPort
item.description:
This trap signifies that a controlled switch's port is loop-detect.
Varbinds: 0. yrSwLoopDetectPortStatus (INTEGER) The current operational state of each controlled switch's loop-detect port.

item.name: SNMP Trap: YAMAHA-RT-SWITCH::yrSwPoESupplyPort
item.description:
This trap signifies that a controlled switch's port is PoE supply.
Varbinds: 0. yrSwPoEPortState (INTEGER) The current state of each controlled switch's PoE port.

item.name: SNMP Trap: YAMAHA-RT-SWITCH::yrSwPoETerminatePort
item.description:
This trap signifies that a controlled switch's port is PoE terminate.
Varbinds: 0. yrSwPoEPortState (INTEGER) The current state of each controlled switch's PoE port.

item.name: yrfConfigFile
item.description: A textual string containing a name of a configuration file which is now executing.

item.name: yrfEnableLoginTrap
item.description: Indicates whether an yrfLoginTrap send when login status is changed.

item.name: yrfFirmwareFile
item.description: A textual string containing a name of a firmware file which is now executing.

item.name: yrfRestart
item.description: A system will restart when the value 'restart' is written to this variable

item.name: yrfRevision
item.description: A textual string containing a revision information of an firmware. This variable is equal to mib-2.system.sysDescr.

item.name: yrfUpTime
item.description: The time (in hundredths of a second) since the network management portion of the system was last re-initialized. This variable is equal to mib-2.system.sysUpTime.

item.name: yrhCpuType
item.description: The CPU type.

item.name: yrhCpuUtil1min
item.description: The average utilization of CPU in 1 minutes.

item.name: yrhCpuUtil1minTrapThreshold
item.description: If the value of the variable cpuUtil1min is over this variable, the system will produce cpuUtilTrap. If this value is set as 0, the system will never send cpuUtilTrap.

item.name: yrhCpuUtil5min
item.description: The average utilization of CPU in 5 minutes.

item.name: yrhCpuUtil5minTrapThreshold
item.description: If the value of the variable cpuUtil5min is over this variable, the system will produce cpuUtilTrap. If this value is set as 0, the system will never send cpuUtilTrap.

item.name: yrhCpuUtil5sec
item.description: The average utilization of CPU in 5 seconds.

item.name: yrhCpuUtil5secTrapThreshold
item.description: If the value of the variable cpuUtil5sec is over this variable, the system will produce cpuUtilTrap. If this value is set as 0, the system will never send cpuUtilTrap.

item.name: yrhEnableSystemAlarmTrap
item.description: Indicate the system will send yrhSystemAlarmTrap when the variable yrhSystemTrap is turned to on.

item.name: yrhFlashROMSize
item.description: The size of the internal Flash ROM in bytes.

item.name: yrhInboxTemperature
item.description: A temperature in the box.

item.name: yrhMemorySize
item.description: The size of main memory in bytes.

item.name: yrhMemoryUtil
item.description: The utilization in percentage of main memory.

item.name: yrhMemoryUtilTrapThreshold
item.description: If the value of the variable yrhMemoryUtil is over this variable, the system will produce yrhMemoryUtilTrap. If this value is set as 0, the system will never send yrhMemoryUtilTrap.

item.name: yrhSystemAlarm
item.description: Indicate the condition when the ALARM LED is on or off.

item.name: enableYrIfIsdnStatusChange
item.description: Indicate that the system will send a trap, yrIfIsdnStatusChange, when the variables, yrIfIsdnStatus, are changed, or not.

item.name: enableYrIfPpLinkTrap
item.description: Indicate that the system will send a trap, yrIfPpLinkUp or yrIfPpLinkDown, when the PP link status change.

item.name: yrIfNumber
item.description: The number of physical and logical network interfaces (regardless of their current state) present on this system.

item.name: yrIfPpDisplayAtMib2
item.description: The flag which the pp interfaces information will be displaied as MIB-2 interfaces object, or not.

item.name: yrIfSwitchDisplayAtMib2
item.description: The flag which the controlled switch's interfaces information will be displaied as MIB-2 interfaces object, or not.

item.name: yrIfTunnelDisplayAtMib2
item.description: The flag which the tunnel interfaces information will be displaied as MIB-2 interfaces object, or not.

item.name: yrSwNumber
item.description: The number of controlled switch on this system.

discovery_rule.description: A list of binding information entries between a high and a low layer interfaces.

item_prototype.name: yrIfBindHighLayer for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: A high layer interface index value of the table yrIfTable.

item_prototype.name: yrIfBindLowLayer for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: A low layer interface index value of the table yrIfTable.

item_prototype.name: yrIfBindStatus for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: A status of the relationship between two high/low layer interfaces.

discovery_rule.name: yrIfBriEntry Discovery
discovery_rule.description: A BRI interface entry.

item_prototype.name: yrIfBriIndex for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: A unique value for each BRI interface. This value is equal to yrIfIndex for a correspond interface.

item_prototype.name: yrIfBriLayer1 for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: A layer 1 status of a BRI interface. If the system has a L1 LED, this variable is equal to a LED status.

item_prototype.name: yrIfBriLED1 for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: A B1 LED status of a BRI interface.

item_prototype.name: yrIfBriLED2 for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: A B2 LED status of a BRI interface.

item_prototype.name: yrIfBriMultiplexNumber for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: A multiplex number of a BRI interface. If this variable's value is N, line speeds of each multiplex is displayed in from yrIfBriMultiplexSpeed1 to yrIfPriMultiplexSpeedN. If the BRI interface is configured as ISDN, this valiable and follows have no mean.

item_prototype.name: yrIfBriMultiplexSpeed1 for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: A line speed in bit/s of a first multiplex of a BRI interface.

item_prototype.name: yrIfBriMultiplexSpeed2 for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: A line speed in bit/s of a first multiplex of a BRI interface.

item_prototype.name: yrIfBriType for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: A line type of a BRI interface.

discovery_rule.name: yrIfClassEntry Discovery
discovery_rule.description: The information about output queue classes.

item_prototype.name: yrIfClassDescr for {#SNMPVALUE}
item_prototype.description: A description of the value of yrIfClassNumber. This string indicates a class number.

item_prototype.name: yrIfClassIfIndex for {#SNMPVALUE}
item_prototype.description: The interface on which this class is belong to. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of yrIfIndex.

item_prototype.name: yrIfClassNumber for {#SNMPVALUE}
item_prototype.description: A class ID of this class. This ID indicates a unique class number.

item_prototype.name: yrIfClassOutDiscards for {#SNMPVALUE}
item_prototype.description: The number of outbound packets which were chosen to be discarded even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being transmitted. One possible reason for discarding such a packet could be to free up buffer space.

item_prototype.name: yrIfClassOutErrors for {#SNMPVALUE}
item_prototype.description: The number of outbound packets that could not be transmitted because of errors.

item_prototype.name: yrIfClassOutOctets for {#SNMPVALUE}
item_prototype.description: The total number of octets transmitted out of the queue.

item_prototype.name: yrIfClassOutPkts for {#SNMPVALUE}
item_prototype.description: The total number of packets transmitted out of the queue.

item_prototype.name: yrIfClassOutQLen for {#SNMPVALUE}
item_prototype.description: The length of the output packet queue (in packets).

discovery_rule.name: yrIfEntry Discovery
discovery_rule.description: A physical interface entry.

item_prototype.name: yrIfDescr for {#SNMPVALUE}
item_prototype.description: A textual string containing information about the interface. This string should include the name of the manufacturer, the product name and the version of the hardware interface.

item_prototype.name: yrIfIndex for {#SNMPVALUE}
item_prototype.description: A unique value for each interface. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of ifNumber. The value for each interface must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re- initialization.

item_prototype.name: yrIfSpecific for {#SNMPVALUE}
item_prototype.description: A reference to MIB definitions specific to the particular media which is indicated by yrIfType.

item_prototype.name: yrIfType for {#SNMPVALUE}
item_prototype.description: The type of an interface.

item_prototype.name: yrIfIsdnBch for {#SNMPINDEX}

item_prototype.name: yrIfIsdnDisconnectReason for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: A disconnect reason which is defined in an ISDN specification, JT-Q931, or else. If a BRI type which is indicated as a variable yrIfBriType or yrIfPriType is leased line, this entry has no meaning.

item_prototype.name: yrIfIsdnIndex for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: A unique value for each BRI or PRI interface. This value is equal to yrIfBriIndex/yrIfPriIndex and yrIfIndex for a correspond interface.

item_prototype.name: yrIfIsdnPeerAddress for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: A peer's ISDN address. If the peer has a sub address, it follows the ISDN number with a separator slash (/). If a line type which is indicated as a variable yrIfBriType or yrIfPriType is leased line, this entry has no meaning.

item_prototype.name: yrIfIsdnStatus for {#SNMPINDEX}
item_prototype.description: ISDN or leased line status. For a BRI interface, this variable links directly with the system's LED, B1 or B2.
